properties.NAME: Steavenson Falls
properties.ACCESS_DSC:
By car, Falls Road (sealed) is a 4km trip from Marysville centre.
Walkers can access the falls reserve from Marysville also, via Tree Fern Gully and the Keppel Walking Tracks.
properties.COMMENTS: Opened to tourists in 1866, the falls drop 84m in three cascades into a picturesque treefern lined gully. A magnificent site both day and night, after dusk the falls are floodlit until 11pm with power from a hydro-electric turbine within the scenic reser
properties.LABEL: Steavenson Falls

properties.NAME: Little Cabbage Tree Creek Falls Picnic Area
properties.ACCESS_DSC: Follow the Murrungowar Forest Drive, turning right onto Tarlton Track.
properties.COMMENTS: Picnic area with a short walk to a viewing platform at the base of the Little Cabbage Tree Creek Falls
properties.PICNICING_C: Tables and fireplaces provided, toilets at site and take off point for the Little Cabbage Tree Walk to the viewing platform at the falls.
properties.LABEL: Little Cabbage Tree Creek Falls Picnic Area

properties.NAME: Richards
properties.COMMENTS: Situated amongst tall eucalypt forest adjacent to Cave Hill Creek, Richards caters for picnickers as well as providing a separate area for campers. Basic amenities of toilets, wood fired BBQ''s are picnic tables are provided.
properties.LABEL: Richards

properties.NAME: Powelltown Picnic Area
properties.ACCESS_DSC: Take the Warburton Highway from Lilydale, turn left at the intersection of the Warburton Highway and the Powelltown/Noojee Rd in Yarra Junction, drive south for approximately 15kms and it is directly opposite the department''s office.
properties.COMMENTS: Near the Little Yarra River and just off Powelltown''''s main street, this site offers facilities for day visitors and access to walks (Walk Into History and Reids Tramline). An old timber bogie used to haul timber from the forests sits in-situ.
properties.PICNICING_C: Near the Little Yarra River and just off Powelltown''s main street, this site offers facilities for day visitors and access to walks (Walk Into History and Reids Tramline). An old timber bogie used to haul timber from the forests sits in-situ.

properties.NAME: Youngs Creek Picnic Area
properties.ACCESS_DSC: Access to this site is via the Bonang Hwy, turning right on to 4 1/2 mile track and following along to Storers track and following signs down to picnic area.Be aware of Log Trucks in the area- frequently go through Picnic Area.
properties.COMMENTS: Formalised picnic ground on the fringes of the Youngs Creek rainforest.
properties.PICNICING_C: BBQ Facilities and picnic tables provided
properties.LABEL: Youngs Creek Picnic Area

properties.ACCESS_DSC: Vicroads Map 88 D5 At Narrawong turn north onto Boyers Rd follow the bitum all the way up the hill when bitum runs out about 500 metres on the left is the entrance to picnic area.
properties.LABEL: Sawpit Picnic Area

properties.NAME: Bilstons Tree
properties.COMMENTS: Bilston's Tree is reputed to be the largest River Red Gum in the world. Thought to be approximately 800 years old, this  tree is on the register of the National Trust.
properties.LABEL: Bilstons Tree

Access via Ensay and Bentley Plain Rd.
Access via Bindi and Nunniong Rd and Bentley Plain Rd
properties.COMMENTS: Campsite with forestry hut. Three walking tracks in area, through Alpine Ash forests and Alpine Bogs
properties.LABEL: Bentley Plain

properties.NAME: Coopers Creek Day Visitor Area Two
properties.LABEL: Coopers Creek Day Visitor Area Two

properties.NAME: Chinamans Campground
properties.COMMENTS: Located in the Mt Cole State Forest Chinamans Campground is an ideal locations to base yourself for several walks in the area.  Native trees in the area include Messmate, Manna Gum and Blue Gums.
properties.LABEL: Chinamans Campground

properties.NAME: Battery Dam Historic Site
properties.ACCESS_DSC: Battery Dam is located 3 km south of Maryborough.  From Maryborough head south along Majorca Road (Inkerman Street).  Once in the Craigie State Forest turn west onto Graves track and head into the forest for approximately 1km.
properties.COMMENTS: Battery Dam offers the visitor a mix of cultural and natural features to explore.  Extensive information is provided on the sites cultural history.  Other activiyies include picnicing, bushwalking and nature observation.
properties.LABEL: Battery Dam Historic Site

properties.NAME: Beeripmo Campground
properties.COMMENTS: The Beeripmo campground is accessible by walkers only. The site is flat, siting high on the plateau and nestled in a natural bushland setting. Facilities include ten camp pads, fireplaces and toilets.
properties.CAMPING_C: The Beeripmo campground is accessible by walkers only. The site is flat, siting high on the plateau and nestled in a natural bushland setting. Facilities include ten camp pads, fireplaces and toilets.
properties.LABEL: Beeripmo Campground

properties.NAME: Firth Park
properties.ACCESS_DSC: Day Use and Campers should not park inside the main access road.
properties.COMMENTS:
Mostly a rec reserve for horse training.
With BBQ facilities and water supplied via tap.
properties.LABEL: Firth Park

properties.NAME: Razorback Hut
properties.COMMENTS: showers and bunk beds.  large horse yard
properties.LABEL: Razorback Hut

properties.NAME: Waanyarra Recreation Site
properties.ACCESS_DSC: Waanyarra is located 8km north of Dunolly.  From Dunolly head north along the Dunolly Bridgewater Road and turn east onto Waanyarra Cemetery Road at the sign.
properties.COMMENTS: Set in the Box Ironbark forests of Central Victoria Waanyarra Recreation Site is a popular camping and picnic ground.  The site is based on the historic township of Waanyarra and offers a range of forest based activities.
properties.LABEL: Waanyarra Recreation Site

properties.NAME: Ben Nevis Picnic Area
properties.HANG_GLD_C: Large sheer mountain with clear take off and large landing paddocks below. Take-off is off a large granite outcrop (natural ground ramp) facing west. Sheer vertical drop of 500 feet.
properties.LABEL: Ben Nevis Picnic Area

properties.NAME: Craigs Hut
properties.COMMENTS: Craigs Hut was originally constructed for the 1983 Australian movie ''The Man from Snowy River'' as the home of Jim Craig, the main character in the movie. The hut was rebuilt in 1993, destroyed by the 2006 Great Divide wildfire and again rebuilt in 2008
properties.LABEL: Craigs Hut

properties.NAME: Buxton Mt Bike Park Trailhead
properties.PICNICING_C: This site provides basic facilities for picnicking and is the major site for accessing the Buxton mountain bike trail network.
properties.LABEL: Buxton Mt Bike Park Trailhead

properties.NAME: Noojee Depot Picnic Area Site
properties.COMMENTS: Located alongside the lovely Latrobe River, this site offers a wonderful place for a picnic. Also the starting point for the Loch Valley Tramline walk.
